    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3241147537" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3241147537" />
    <a title="Philip Horspool" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102467142-philip-horspool"><img alt="Philip Horspool" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3241147537?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Philip Horspool" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Philip Horspool" href="/user/show/102467142-philip-horspool">Philip Horspool</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3241147537" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4788914326528011678">Any Chomsky poliical/economic work is a 5 star in my eyes and this is no exception. Chomsky dissects with accuracy a range of issues and the focus in this book is on some familiar areas - Israel/Palestine, Central America but i particularly thought the chapter on the failure of the US to uphold democracy in its own country enlightening. Chomsky is a living genius who atands up and questions those who wield power in a world where the majority of intellectuals fail totally in this respect. We are </span>
  <span id="freeText4788914326528011678" style="display:none">Any Chomsky poliical/economic work is a 5 star in my eyes and this is no exception. Chomsky dissects with accuracy a range of issues and the focus in this book is on some familiar areas - Israel/Palestine, Central America but i particularly thought the chapter on the failure of the US to uphold democracy in its own country enlightening. Chomsky is a living genius who atands up and questions those who wield power in a world where the majority of intellectuals fail totally in this respect. We are lucky to have him and it is essntial we listen to him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4788914326528011678" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

