<div id="review_2441909395" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2441909395" />
    <a title="Catnaitab" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15737902-catnaitab"><img alt="Catnaitab" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2441909395?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Catnaitab" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Catnaitab" href="/user/show/15737902-catnaitab">Catnaitab</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141023038" href="/book/show/863473.Failed_States">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15737902-catnaitab?shelf=politics">politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15737902-catnaitab?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2441909395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1021909680571613950">This book mostly made me sad about the state of our world nowadays and how the policy-makers in the US, do not respect anything or anyone, but the money dem making. Which I guess happens in a lot of other places in the world. The facts given by Noam Chomsky are extremely interesting to follow and easy to understand. However especially in the first half of the book it seems to jump a bit too fast between several examples of the US behaviour, not explain well enough or just change the direction to</span>
  <span id="freeText1021909680571613950" style="display:none">This book mostly made me sad about the state of our world nowadays and how the policy-makers in the US, do not respect anything or anyone, but the money dem making. Which I guess happens in a lot of other places in the world. The facts given by Noam Chomsky are extremely interesting to follow and easy to understand. However especially in the first half of the book it seems to jump a bit too fast between several examples of the US behaviour, not explain well enough or just change the direction too often. In the end I left convinced that the US is a failed state and that hypocrisy rules the (ruling) world, so Noam accomplished his goal.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1021909680571613950" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

